 interests, Godfrey gathers voices from the found texts, and adds others, in defence of the natural world. Interconnected, Godfrey's poems are a choral and visual, literal representation of how industry, capitalism, and colonialism seek to erase affected peoples and their voices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCanadian poetryy21st century. 0aEnvironmental responsibilityvPoetry. 0aIndigenous peoplesvPoetry. 0aMineral industriesxCorrupt practicesvPoetry. 0aProtest movementsvPoetry. 7aPOETRY / Canadian.2bisacsh  aCanadian poetry.  aCapitalism poetry.  aColonial.  aDecolonize.  aEarth Day.  aEnvironmental books.  aEnvironmentalism.  aMidwest.  aNature poetry.  aOskana poetry.  aPoetry books.  aPoetry collection.  aRabbit Lake.  aRadioactive.  aSaskatchewan.  aSettler.  aUranium.  abooks poetry.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311127221408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021z978311127464540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978088977841240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889778412423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889778412/original  a978-3-11-127221-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-127464-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles